4.00	Herbert_Vere_Evatt	H. V. Evatt	Herbert Vere Evatt, QC KStJ (30 April 1894 – 2 November 1965), was an Australian jurist, politician and writer. He was President of the United Nations General Assembly in 1948–49 and helped draft the United Nations Universal Declaration of Human Rights (1948). He was Leader of the Australian Labor Party (and thus Leader of the Opposition) from 1951 to 1960.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/f8/EvattALP.jpg/220px-EvattALP.jpg
